BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 5 April, TASS -- U.N. Secretary General 
Butrus Butrus-Ghali has described his talks with Russian leaders 
as constructive. Upon winding up his five-day official visit, 
he left here for Minsk on Tuesday. At the airport he was seen 
off by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. 
  In a brief ITAR-TASS interview before departure, the U.N. 
chief said he postively assesses the results of the visit. 
Russia renders effective assistance to U.N. activities to keep 
peace and settle crisis situations, he emphasised. 

